# Console Agent - Project Intelligence

## Project Overview
- **Package:** @consoleag/console-agent
- **Purpose:** Drop-in agentic workflows via `console.agent(...)` â€” as easy as console.log()
- **License:** MIT
- **AI Provider:** Google Gemini (v1.0 only)

## Key Architecture Decisions
- Bundler: tsup (dual ESM/CJS)
- AI SDK: Vercel AI SDK (`ai` + `@ai-sdk/google`)
- Console styling: chalk v5 + ora v8
- Testing: vitest
- Config: module-level singleton pattern
- console.agent is a Proxy-based callable with persona methods

## Development Patterns
- All source in `src/`, tests in `tests/`
- TypeScript strict mode
- Fire-and-forget is default execution mode
- Personas auto-detect from prompt keywords
- Budget/rate-limiting via token bucket algorithm

## Important Constraints
- v1.0: Google provider ONLY (no OpenAI/Anthropic)
- No streaming, no multi-turn, no custom tools API
- Node.js only (no browser support)
- Must work with zero config (sensible defaults)
